Puppet glossary:

Puppet master: the master server that controlls configuration on the nodes
Puppet Agent Node: a node controlled by a puppet master
Manifest: a file that ends in .pp and contains a set of instructions to be executed
Resource: blocks of code that declare elements on the system that need to be changed
Module: collection of manifests
Class: similar to classes in OOP and can be used for encapsulation of resources.
	Classes are containers of different resources.
Facts: global vars containing information about the system (similar to facts in Ansible)
Servces: they trigger status changes of services on nodes (similar to handlers in Ansible)

get resource description:
puppet describe file

get list of available resources:
puppet describe --list

search for modules in Puppet forge:
puppet module search rvm

